				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">You can always try rendering to video overlays instead of the regular back-buffer. These basically provide an independent swapping chain on top of the regular display, typically used for video playback by media players.<br /><br />There's plenty of downsides though. They're optional, have only one channel, use hardware-dependent YUV formats, are unsupported on Vista, use a new interface on Windows 7, won't work across multiple-monitors, etc.<br /><br />If you're dead-set on avoiding tearing at all costs then they're probably the way to go. Just be sure to have a fallback.<br /><br />Or, you know, just pray your users have Aero enabled and a properly configured system..</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

